data.current_description: Batch gets the update history of assets that overlap a time window. For IAM_POLICY content, this API outputs history when the asset and its attached IAM POLICY both exist. This can create gaps in the output history. Otherwise, this API outputs history with asset in both non-delete or deleted status. If a specified asset does not exist, this API returns an INVALID_ARGUMENT error.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve asset update history within time window
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves the update history of multiple assets within a specified time window. For IAM_POLICY content, history is output only when both the asset and its attached IAM policy exist, which may create gaps. For other content types, history includes assets in both active and deleted states. Requires asset names and time window parameters. Returns a BatchGetAssetsHistoryResponse containing temporal asset data. Returns INVALID_ARGUMENT error if specified assets do not exist.

data.current_description: Exports assets with time and resource types to a given Cloud Storage location. The output format is newline-delimited JSON. This API implements the google.longrunning.Operation API allowing you to keep track of the export. We recommend intervals of at least 2 seconds with exponential retry to poll the export operation result. For regular-size resource parent, the export operation usually finishes within 5 minutes.
data.summary_suggestion: Export assets to Cloud Storage asynchronously
data.description_suggestion: Exports assets filtered by time and resource types to a specified Cloud Storage location. Requires ExportAssetsRequest with parent resource, output configuration, and optional asset/resource type filters. Output is formatted as newline-delimited JSON. This is an asynchronous operation that returns an Operation resource for tracking progress. Poll the operation at intervals of at least 2 seconds with exponential retry. Typical completion time is 5 minutes for regular-size resource parents. Side effects: Creates exported asset data in the specified Cloud Storage location.
